ğŸ§  MASSA SMART CONTRACT DESIGN

Weâ€™ll split logic into 3 core contracts (or 1 with modules, but logically 3):

TeamRegistry â€“ teams + members + percentages

PaymentSplitter â€“ receives funds & splits payments

Governance â€“ proposals and voting for split changes

And ASC behavior:

Auto-exec proposals after deadline

Auto-generate monthly summaries (optional)

1ï¸âƒ£ TeamRegistry Contract

Stores:

Team {
  id: u64;
  owner: string;       // creator of the team
  metadataURI: string; // name, description stored in JSON off-chain
  isActive: bool;
}

TeamMember {
  teamId: u64;
  member: string;
  percentage: u16;     // e.g. 2000 = 20.00% if using basis points
  role: string;
}


Key functions:

createTeam(metadataURI: string): u64
addMember(teamId: u64, member: string, percentage: u16, role: string)
removeMember(teamId: u64, member: string)
getTeam(teamId: u64): Team
getMembers(teamId: u64): TeamMember[]


Validation:

Total percentages for a team must always sum to 100% (or 10,000 bp).

2ï¸âƒ£ PaymentSplitter Contract

Handles actual receipt & distribution of funds.

Core function when client pays:

payTeam(teamId: u64, reference: string) // msg.value = amount


Logic:

Ensure teamId exists & active

Read all TeamMember entries

For each member:

memberShare = amount * percentage / 10000

Option A: send immediately (transfer(member, memberShare))

Option B: add to internal balance:

balances[member] += memberShare;


Store Payment struct for history.

If using internal balances, we expose:

withdrawMyEarnings()
getMyBalance(): u64

3ï¸âƒ£ Governance Contract (for split changes)

Data:

Proposal {
  id: u64;
  teamId: u64;
  creator: string;
  newAllocations: Allocation[]; // { member, percentage }
  endTime: u64;
  yesVotes: u32;
  noVotes: u32;
  executed: bool;
}

Allocation {
  member: string;
  percentage: u16;
}


Functions:

createSplitProposal(teamId, newAllocations[], reasonURI)
voteOnProposal(proposalId, support)
executeProposal(proposalId) // called by ASC when endTime reached


Who can vote?

Members of that team (including owner)

How ASC fits in:

We schedule an autonomous call that periodically runs:

checkAndExecuteProposals()


This function:

Finds proposals where endTime <= now AND executed == false

If yesVotes > noVotes â†’ updates TeamRegistry percentages

Sets executed = true

No one needs to manually trigger execution â†’ fully autonomous governance.

ğŸ” AUTONOMOUS BEHAVIOR (ASC) SUMMARY

Massaâ€™s ASC can:

Regularly scan proposals & auto-execute approved ones.

Auto-generate monthly summary stats:

Total paid per team

Total paid per member
(you can store counters on-chain for quick access)

Optionally, auto-disable inactive teams (no payment in X months).

All of this can be done via scheduled/deferred calls in Massa.

